[1] Philippines (Sarangani)
Date: 23 Jul 2004
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Minda News 22 Jul 2004 [edited]
<http://www.mindanews.com/2004/07/22nws-dengue.html>

Dengue outbreak hits Sarangani town
------------------------------------
Health officials in Sarangani province have declared an outbreak of
dengue hemorrhagic fever. The outbreak has already killed at least 4
children in 5 villages in the capital town of Alabel. Cornelia
Baldelovar, officer-in-charge of the Sarangani provincial health
office, said the mosquito-borne disease has afflicted at least 19
children since the rainy season started last month [June 2004].
Citing a report from Dr. Honorato Fabio, Alabel municipal health
officer Baldelovar said the affected barangays are Poblacion,
Maribulan, Alegria, Spring, and Kawas.
Based on its monitoring, conducted from 6 Jun - 12 Jul 2004, most of
the cases happened in the Poblacion area, where 11 children were
affected. "We consider the situation now as alarming, since the
number of recorded cases already constitutes an outbreak," Baldelovar
said.
Baldelovar said the Alabel municipal government already conducted
fogging operations to help contain further spread of the disease. She
said the municipal health office has also sought the immediate
allocation of P 200 000 [USD 3600] for the purchase of medicines for
the affected children, most of whom are confined to the district
hospital here. Baldelovar said they have also launched an information
campaign, at the barangay level, about the disease and about some
possible remedial measures.
She said they particularly instructed residents to remove all
possible breeding places of mosquitoes inside, and outside, of their
houses, such as tin cans, rubber tires, and bottles, or, drain
accumulated water from trees and plants.
[Byline: Allen V. Estabillo]
